<p>
    <strong>From the college:</strong>
    <i>Students who have completed advanced work in secondary school in one or more
academic areas may earn advanced standing. Students who received a score of 3, 4 or 5
in Advanced Placement Examinations will be granted advanced placement and college
credit. Students who received a score of 1 or 2 are not eligible for exemption or college
credit.</i>
